2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 Article – Environment
5 9–283.
6 (a) (1) Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, by regulation, the
7 Department shall establish and collect a fee to be paid by a generator of coal combustion
8 by–products[, based on a].
9 (2) THE BASE FEE ESTABLISHED BY THE DEPARTMENT UNDER THIS
10 SUBSECTION MAY NOT BE LESS THAN $2.30 per ton [rate] of coal combustion
11 by–products generated by the generator annually.
12 (b) The Department shall base the fees on the following factors:
13 (1) The total annual tonnage of coal combustion by–products that the
14 generator generates;
15 (2) The type and volume of coal combustion by–products generated by the
16 generator;
17 (3) Whether the generator uses or disposes of the coal combustion
18 by–products;
19 (4) To the extent that the coal combustion by–products are used rather
20 than disposed of, the types of the uses;
21 (5) Whether the coal combustion by–products are transported for use or
22 disposal out–of–state; [and]
23 (6) THE VOLUME OF COAL COMBUSTION BY–PRODUCTS THAT HAVE
24 BEEN DISPOSED OF AND REMAIN IN LANDFILLS OR OTHER STORAGE UNITS IN THE
25 STATE THAT ARE SUBJECT TO INSPECTION AND MONITORING, NOT INCLUDING COAL
26 COMBUSTION BY–PRODUCTS THAT HAVE BEEN:
27 (I) ADDED TO CEMENT PRODUCTS;
28 (II) USED IN COAL MINE RECLAMATION; OR
29 (III) BENEFICIALLY REUSED IN A MANNER ACCEPTABLE TO THE
30 DEPARTMENT; AND

