1 (3) ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE POWER PLANT RESEARCH
2 PROGRAM IN THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES; AND
3 (4) THREE MEMBERS, APPOINTED BY THE SECRETARY, EACH WITH
4 TECHNICAL EXPERTISE IN ONE OF THE FOLLOWING SUBJECTS:
5 (I) COAL COMBUSTION BY–PRODUCTS;
6 (II) PUBLIC HEALTH; AND
7 (III) WATER QUALITY.
8 (D) THE SECRETARY SHALL DESIGNATE THE CHAIR OF THE COORDINATING
9 COMMITTEE.
10 (E) THE DEPARTMENT AND THE POWER PLANT RESEARCH PROGRAM IN
11 THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES SHALL JOINTLY PROVIDE STAFF FOR
12 THE COORDINATING COMMITTEE.
13 (F) A MEMBER OF THE COORDINATING COMMITTEE:
14 (1) MAY NOT RECEIVE COMPENSATION AS A MEMBER OF THE
15 COORDINATING COMMITTEE; BUT
16 (2) IS ENTITLED TO REIMBURSEMENT FOR EXPENSES UNDER THE
17 STANDARD STATE TRAVEL REGULATIONS, AS PROVIDED IN THE STATE BUDGET.
18 (G) THE COORDINATING COMMITTEE SHALL:
19 (1) BEGINNING IN 2026, MEET AT LEAST TWICE A YEAR, AT THE TIMES
20 AND PLACES THAT THE COORDINATING COMMITTEE DETERMINES; AND
21 (2) WITH RESPECT TO COAL COMBUSTION BY–PRODUCT SITES:
22 (I) SHARE INFORMATION ON MONITORING RESULTS; AND
23 (II) DISCUSS REMEDIAL ACTION THAT IS IN PROCESS, THAT IS
24 STILL REQUIRED, OR BOTH.
25 (H) ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 1, 2026, AND EACH OCTOBER 1 THEREAFTER,
26 THE COORDINATING COMMITTEE SHALL REPORT ITS FINDINGS DURING THE
27 IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING CALENDAR YEAR TO THE SENATE COMMITTEE ON
